I’m very excited about what you are doing - no hate, but there is no such thing as vegan leather. “Vegan leather” is simply the result of decades of evolution of the pleather (plasticized synthetic leather). Plastic polymers polyurethane (PU) and polyvinyl chloride (PVC) are the most commonly used to produce faux leather fabrics. The term “vegan leather” was created by fast fashion as a cheaper and more public appealing alternative to real leather. Things need to be named for what they really are. Especially in fashion, transparency is the key.
